children.subject: I would second this saying you should take Rao exams to practice if he is teaching. I took the 70 with prof Sahai and the best way to study was to do sp20 hw rather than any practice problem or test. I think it'd be best to fully understand the 70 concepts with the Sahai level sp20 hw, then do Rao tests to see if you understand the material if your goal is to learn more and do well on the test. If your main goal is to just get a good grade on the test, probably doing just Rao tests would be fine.

Just to add..the most recent offering of 70 in Spring 2020..was significantly different in terms of the way questions were asked on the exams - this was both before and after COVID impacted our lives. If you see midterm 1..Professor Sahai's way of writing questions is different from Rao's and even the format changed. However, the HWs from Spring 2020 are one of the best ways you can prepare for CS 70. They will help you internalize the 70 material in a much better way than a standard offering of 70 would.
